  It's still useful after you have Transon's Infusion.  If you are fighting a summoning mob, it is a bit tough to chain cast pets.  So you chain cast Transon's heal with the new level 44 one and slip in a nuke when you can.  I use these two spells to solo the corrupt seafury in OOT.  Before I bought the 44 heal, I wouldn't try the corrupt solo.  Of course, if you have the level 60 heal, the 44 heal probably isn't much use to you.  <br>
