<br>
When I use my air pet, I fully buff/armor it and like to keep it alive because it tanks really well.  Because 44th level is focused, I find it a better heal to use than the 52? level heal.  I find I can tank bigger things by alternating the 44th heal and a nuke than the 52? level heal.  <br>
<br>
The unfocused 52? heal takes longer to cast, uses more mana, and its efficiency is worse than a focused 44th level spell even though it is a slightly larger heal.  The 52? burns too much of my mana which then prevents me from nuking.  <br>
<br>
I find the 44th Heal spell very valuable. It is still my primary heal spell even though I have the 52? level heal.  In situations where I might need to chain heal, I load the 52? spell as well.  <br>
<br>
