.  I know of no easy way to post that information in its entirety in a readable format so I am just going to summarize it.  <br>
<br>
Listed below are the focus effect/spell combinations used to calculate the summary information in the lower table.  Also listed is a a code to match the Spell and Focus information to the summary information.  <br>
<br>
        Focus effects<br>
Imprvd&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Mana&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Spell&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Healing&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Pres&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Haste     Spell   (Code)<br>
0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15       Renew Summoning (RNS)<br>
0.2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15       Renew Summoning (RNSF)<br>
0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Refresh Summoning(RFS)<br>
0.2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Refresh Summoning(RFSF)<br>
0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Transon's Infusion  (TI)<br>
0.2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Transon's Infusion  (TIF)<br>
0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Transon's Renewal  (TR)<br>
0.2&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.1&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.15&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Transon's Renewal  (TRF)<br>
0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 0.0&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Planar Renewal (PR)<br>
<br>
The F at the end basically means includes a Improved Healing focus item has been included.  It is not possible to show all the different combinations of focus items/spells so I have chosen the ones I thought would be of most interest.  I have included spell haste and Mana preservation on most items because at the levels of those spells, these items are easily obtained and should be in use.  I decided to separate out the Improved Healing focus because these items are more difficult to obtain and the value of these items is of more interest.  <br>
<br>
This table has the summary information for the spells listed in the above table in the same order as the above table.  For the spells that were variable by level, I calculated the information based upon being 53rd level.  {My level when I performed this analysis.}  The lower level spells increase their max heal by two points per level, but the values in the table only change marginally from the 53rd level values and the difference between the values at different levels stays virtually the same. <br>
 <br>
<br>
                          Heal/      Cast                               Spell<br>
HP         Mana    &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Mana      Rev&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Time to&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Mana to  Code<br>
Healed&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Cost&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ratio&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Time&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2400&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2400       <br>
206.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 90.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.29&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 10.48&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 125.70&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1080.00  RNS<br>
247.20&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 90.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.75&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 10.48&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 104.75&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 900.00    RNSF<br>
356.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 180.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1.98&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 10.48&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 73.33&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1260.00  RFS<br>
427.20&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 180.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.37&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 10.48&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 62.85&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1080.00  RFSF<br>
557.85&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 247.50&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.25&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 11.75&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 58.75&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1237.50   TI<br>
669.42&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 247.50&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.70&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 11.75&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 47.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 990.00    TIF<br>
900&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 400&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 2.25&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 14.5&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 43.5&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1200       TR<br>
1080.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 360.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 3.00&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 13.45&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 40.35&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 1080.00* TRF<br>
1200&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 300&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 4&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 14.5&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 29&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 600         PR<br>
<br>
 <br>
Headings            Description<br>
Heal                  The amount the spell heals.<br>
Mana                 Adjusted mana cost.{See above table for adj %.<br>
Heal/Mana Ratio  The Healing efficiency.<br>
Cast Rev Time    Time to cast   recast time<br>
Time to 2400.     How long to heal 2400 pts using this spell only<br>
Mana to 2400.    How much mana used to heal at least 2400pt <br>
<br>
*This value is larger than some of the lower efficiency spells because of the mana wasted due to overhealing to get to 2400pts or larger.  <br>
<br>
<br>
What does this table tell us.<br>
<br>
1.  Our first heal is our most efficient heal until we get an improved healing focused 60 heal spell or we get the 65th pet heal spell.  <br>
<br>
2.  The Refresh Summoning spell heals 40% faster than the Renew Summoning but is only 90% as efficient.  {I think that increase in heal speed overweighs it being less efficient}<br>
<br>
3. An Improved Healing focused Refresh Summoning spell heals at nearly the same rate as an unfocused Transon's Infusion, but is slightly more efficient.   <br>
<br>
4.  An Improved Healing focus increasing the Hit Points to Mana ration by ~0.5.  <br>
<br>
<br>
How does this effect what I am currently doing.  <br>
<br>
I will continue to use Refresh Summoning in combat until I get an Improved Healing III item at which Time I will switch to Transon's Infusion.<br>
<br>
If healing out of combat, I will remem Renew summoning because if its greater efficiency.<br>
<br>
Hope this analysis helps you.<br>
<br>
PS<br>
Note, if you want to heal as fast as possible, these spell have a 7.5 recast time and having two memed allows you to cast the other while waiting for the first to recycle.  This will greatly increase both the amount of healing and your mana burn rate.  <br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
